text.__SUMMARY__:
Grevillea annulifera, also known as prickly plume grevillea, is a shrub which is endemic to  Western Australia. It grows to between 1 and 4 metres in height and produces white, cream or yellow flowers between June and October (early winter to mid spring) in its native range.The species was formally described in 1864 by botanist Ferdinand von Mueller, based on plant material collected near the Murchison River.
